frameDefinitions: An Agent causes an Explosive device to explode.
These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge, usually directing the projectile from the barrel of the Firearm (the Source), along a Path, and to a Goal.
A Killer or Cause causes the death of the Victim.
An Assailant physically attacks a Victim (which is usually but not always sentient), causing or intending to cause the Victim physical damage.
frameExamples: Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
The Germans wouldn't stop <t>shooting</t> cannons at them.
As soon as he stepped out of the bar he was <t>set</t> upon by four men in ski-masks.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> detonates the <fen>Explosive</fen>.
The <fen>Explosive</fen> causes damage to surrounding objects when operated by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> detonates the <fen>Explosive</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> detonates the <fen>Explosive</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
The self-directed entity that uses and activates the <fen>Firearm</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Firearm</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> activates so that it rapidly propels a projectile.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> fires the <fen>Firearm</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the Agent intentionally affects the Patient.
The person or sentient entity that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The living entity that dies as a result of the killing.
An inanimate entity or process that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The method or action that the <fen>Killer</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> performs resulting in the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The device used by the <fen>Killer</fen> to bring about the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The point or period of time within which the <fen>Victim</fen> is killed.
The location where the death took place.
This role is the being or entity that is injured by the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Assailant</fen> attacks the <fen>Victim</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Assailant</fen> makes an assault on the <fen>Victim</fen>.
